"&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;&#xa0;House of Commons Select Committee\n: Inquiry on&#xa0;the UK’s Development Work in the Middle EastWritten evidence submitted by Save a Child’s Heart (SACH)&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;EXECUTIVE SUMMARYSave a \nChild’\ns Heart (SACH)\n \nwelcomes the opportunity to \nrespond to the House of Commons Select Committee inquiry on the UK’s Development Work in the Middle East. SACH \nis an international, non-g\novernmental, non-political, \nnon-profit\n organization founded in \n1996 in\n Holon, Israel \nat the Wolfson Medical \nCentre\n (\nWMC) with the mission of improving the quality of \npaediatric\n cardiac care for children from low to lower-middle income countries suffering from rheumatic and congenital heart disease and creating \ncentres\n of com\npetence in these countries. \nSACH is fully dedicated to the idea that every child deserves the best medical treatment available, regardless of the child's nationality, religion, race, gender or financial situation. \nDue to the fact that over 50% of the child\nren, who receive cardiac care from SACH, reside in the West Bank and Gaza, it is of significance for SACH\n to respond to this inquiry.\nINTRODUCTION AND BACKGROUNDTHOUGHTS AND RECOMMENDATIONS&#xa0;\nFor further information please contact:\nSimon Fisher, Adv.\nExecutive Director\nSave a Child’s Heart\nEmail: \ndirector@saveachildsheart.org\nTelephone: (972) 3 558 9656\n&#xa0;\n&#xa0;\n.\n&#xa0;\n"